[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{This is the companion hand to Deal 18.

Again, SOUTH uses RKCB after the 4-4 \S fit is discovered. 
This time NORTH shows two Key Cards without the \SQ.

Now SOUTH realizes that in addition to one outside Ace, there is a very possible loser 
in trumps. So she stops at 5\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "W:732.AKQ864.53.87 Q96.32.QJ84.JT63 AK4.J95.AK76.A54 JT85.T7.T92.KQ92"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
2H pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{The chances of a slam on this hand are very small, and if EAST decides to use RKCB it will 
just confuse matters when WEST shows two Key Cards.

EAST has a better way to find out about the hand. She bids 2NT asking WEST to further describe 
his hand. WEST should then bid 3NT, showing a solid suit headed by AKQ.

WEST cannot have as much as an extra Jack, so EAST just passes 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:AQJ862.KQ7.KQJ.A T9.T84.A963.QT73 K53.A952.854.654 74.J63.T72.KJ982"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "6S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
2C pass 2D pass 2S pass 3S pass 4NT pass 5H pass 6S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH realizes NORTH has fewer than 8 points, but the 3\S support bid is enough 
for her to try a RKCB 4NT bid.

NORTH shows two Key Cards and SOUTH figures they will be the \SK and one of the 
red Aces. So she bids 6\S. If instead the Key Cards are the two red Aces SOUTH 
might possibly make all thirteen tricks with a finesse.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:KQJ5.AK652.6.AKQ T93.T3.KT432.T75 A72.Q74.985.9843 864.J98.AQJ7.J62"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 3H pass 4NT pass 5C pass 5D pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST's 3\H bid is "encouraging" so WEST bids 4NT.

When EAST shows one Key Card, (an Ace), WEST is afraid he may have a trump loser as well the 
other Ace. To find out about the \HQ he 
bids 5\D, the Queen Ask.

EAST has the \HQ but no King so she jumps 
to 6\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "N:KQJ5.AK652.6.AKQ T98.T.KQ942.T975 A72.J9874.85.843 643.Q3.AJT73.J62"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 3H pass 4NT pass 5C pass 5D pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{This is the companion to Deal 22.

Again, worried about a possible trump loser in addition to the missing Ace, NORTH 
bids 5\D, the Queen Ask.

SOUTH definitely does NOT have the \HQ. But with five trumps she 
does know that NORTH probably does not have a trump loser so she jumps 
to 6\H anyway.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "6"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:85.KQ964.73.AK85 JT7.32.AJ94.QT72 AK963.AJ75.KQ2.6 Q42.T8.T865.J943"]
